          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5 Tips for Getting Maximum Value from Base44",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After building over a dozen apps on the platform, here's what I've learned:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Be Specific in Your Descriptions",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "\"Build me an app\" gives you something generic. \"Build a task management app with three boards—Product, Marketing, and Design—each with columns for To Do, In Progress, and Done, plus the ability to assign team members and set due dates\" gives you something you'll actually use.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Use Plan Mode for Anything Complex",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If your app has more than three features or multiple user roles, enable Plan Mode first. Review the structure. Adjust. Then let it build. You'll save iteration cycles.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Iterate Through Conversation",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Don't expect perfection on the first generation. Treat it like working with a developer: \"Add a dark mode toggle.\" \"Make the sidebar collapsible.\" \"Add search functionality to the dashboard.\" Each instruction refines the app.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. Start with a Template Idea",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Base44 showcases starter concepts—Reporting Dashboard, Networking App, Room Visualizer. Pick one that's close to what you need, then customize. It's faster than starting from scratch.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. Think About Data from Day One",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Your app is only as useful as the data it manages. Before you start, sketch out what information your app needs to store, display, and process. Feed that into your description for a much stronger foundation.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
